WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.325 --> 00:00:02.288
The VHA provides healthcare

2
00:00:02.288 --> 00:00:05.354
to nearly six million Veterans and their families,

3
00:00:05.354 --> 00:00:08.287
and it is well known that VHA Logistics

4
00:00:08.287 --> 00:00:11.512
is a major contributor to the mission of VHA.

5
00:00:11.512 --> 00:00:13.509
In addition to running the supply chain

6
00:00:13.509 --> 00:00:15.875
for the Veterans Health Administration,

7
00:00:15.875 --> 00:00:19.932
VHA Logistics also provide equipment management support

8
00:00:19.932 --> 00:00:23.366
to VBA and NCA, under the auspices

9
00:00:23.366 --> 00:00:27.658
of an established memorandum of understanding, or MOU,

10
00:00:27.658 --> 00:00:29.738
between the three administrations.

11
00:00:29.738 --> 00:00:31.561
It is important to understand

12
00:00:31.561 --> 00:00:34.808
the relationship these areas have with each other,

13
00:00:34.808 --> 00:00:37.506
and how they contribute across the supply chain.

14
00:00:37.506 --> 00:00:40.306
Select each box in the organizational chart

15
00:00:40.306 --> 00:00:43.737
to learn more about these logistical areas and roles.
